    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ac3ea59a_313083d3",
        "filename": "util/win/process_structs.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 326,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-12T21:55:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The fact that \u003cwinternl.h\u003e declares Reserved2 as [399] and you’re increasing it to [402] is an indication that something’s fishy. At the very least, this field isn’t being treated as the “remainder” of Reserved2, it’s being used to host something more than Reserved2.\n\nI think that the confusion stems from the fact that \u003cwinternl.h\u003e’s TEB (which this is supposed to mirror and expand on) begins with a 12-pointer Reserved1 then a pointer ProcessEnvironmentBlock before reaching Reserved2. NT_TIB accounts for the first 7 of those 13 pointers. Then we put ProcessEnvironmentBlock at ptr[7], where \u003cwinternl.h\u003e would have it at ptr[12]. And that’s just looking at the public header. Consulting the header you referenced from wine, and “dt ntdll!_TEB”, I can see that we’ve got ClientId in the wrong spot altogether It should be between NtTib and ProcessEnvironmentBlock, with some other fields on either side.\n\nTo put it another way, it appears that our ideas of ProcessEnvironmentBlock, and really this entire structure, are also incorrect.\n\nWe never caught this because it appears that this struct is only used with sizeof() (which is incorrect, but might not have been a visible problem because it’s only used to specify the size of the TEB to capture, and capturing a few bytes extra probably wouldn’t have hurt anything most of the time) and to check ClientId (which lies in the correct spot due to our misplaced ProcessEnvironmentBlock).\n\nHere’s how it appears our version should be laid out, expanding everything in Reserved1 since we want ClientId, and otherwise remaining true to \u003cwinternl.h\u003e’s definition:\n\n  NT_TIB\u003cTraits\u003e NtTib;\n  typename Traits::Pointer EnvironmentPointer;\n  CLIENT_ID\u003cTraits\u003e ClientId;\n  typename Traits::Pointer ActiveRpcHandle;\n  typename Traits::Pointer ThreadLocalStoragePointer;\n  typename Traits::Pointer ProcessEnvironmentBlock;\n  typename Traits::Pointer Reserved2[399];\n  BYTE Reserved3[1952];\n  typename Traits::Pointer TlsSlots[64];\n  …\n\nIt would also be good to have a test of some sort for this. Leonard and I were talking about having a more automated way to verify these.",
      "revId": "a3ee9021f355b50e9b438bbbd03e7e55b5560e98",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
